Here's a clear and updated guide to install Android Studio in Ubuntu:

‚úÖ Method 1: Install via Snap (Recommended for Beginners)
This is the simplest method.
üîπ Step 1: Open Terminal (Ctrl + Alt + T)
üîπ Step 2: Run this command:

sudo snap install android-studio --classic
‚úÖ This will automatically download and install the latest Android Studio.

‚úÖ Method 2: Manual Installation from Official Site
üîπ Step 1: Install Java (Required)

sudo apt update
sudo apt install openjdk-17-jdk
üîπ Step 2: Download Android Studio
Go to:
üìé https://developer.android.com/studio
Download the Linux .tar.gz file.
Or use terminal:


wget https://redirector.gvt1.com/edgedl/android/studio/ide-zips/2023.2.1.21/android-studio-2023.2.1.21-linux.tar.gz
üîπ Step 3: Extract the file

tar -xvzf android-studio-*.tar.gz
üîπ Step 4: Move to /opt

sudo mv android-studio /opt/
üîπ Step 5: Launch Android Studio

/opt/android-studio/bin/studio.sh
‚úÖ Follow the setup wizard (Install SDK, configure emulator, etc.)

‚úÖ (Optional) Create Desktop Shortcut
To launch it from the app menu:

sudo nano /usr/share/applications/android-studio.desktop
Paste:
ini
CopyEdit
[Desktop Entry]
Version=1.0
Type=Application
Name=Android Studio
Exec=/opt/android-studio/bin/studio.sh
Icon=/opt/android-studio/bin/studio.png
Categories=Development;IDE;
Terminal=false
Save and exit. Then:

chmod +x /usr/share/applications/android-studio.desktop

‚úÖ Verify Installation
You can now open Android Studio from the Application menu or by running:

android-studio















To create and run Dart programs in Android Studio on Ubuntu, follow this clear step-by-step guide:

‚úÖ Step 1: Install Dart Plugin in Android Studio
1.	Open Android Studio.
2.	Go to Settings or Preferences:
‚Ä¢	Linux/Ubuntu: File > Settings
‚Ä¢	Or use shortcut: Ctrl + Alt + S
3.	Navigate to: Plugins
4.	Search for Dart in the Marketplace.
5.	Click Install.
6.	Also install Flutter plugin if you plan to use Flutter.
7.	Restart Android Studio after installation.

‚úÖ Step 2: Create a Dart Project
1.	On the Android Studio welcome screen, click:
‚ÄúNew Project‚Äù > ‚ÄúDart‚Äù (If Flutter is installed, choose "New Flutter Project")
2.	Choose:
‚Ä¢	Dart Console Application
3.	Specify the project location.
4.	Set Dart SDK path:
‚Ä¢	If not installed, Android Studio may prompt to download the Dart SDK.
‚Ä¢	Or you can manually install Dart using:

sudo apt update
sudo apt install apt-transport-https
sudo sh -c 'wget -qO- https://dl-ssl.google.com/linux/linux_signing_key.pub | apt-key add -'
sudo sh -c 'wget -qO- https://storage.googleapis.com/download.dartlang.org/linux/debian/dart_stable.list > /etc/apt/sources.list.d/dart_stable.list'
sudo apt update
sudo apt install dart

‚úÖ Step 4: Write and Run Dart Program
Example Dart Program:

void main() {
  print("Hello, Dart!");
}
To run:
‚Ä¢	Click the green play ‚ñ∂Ô∏è button in Android Studio, or
‚Ä¢	Open terminal and run:

dart run

‚úÖ Step 5: (Optional) Run Dart in Terminal
To check Dart installation:

dart --version
Run any .dart file directly:
dart hello.dart

